For more info and specific questions about Bauman's event, you can contact them at their website www.baumanfarms.com, phone (503) 792-3524, or Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/baumansfarmandgarden/

Two more days until we are at Bauman's having a great family fun social. The weather looks to be on our side for this event so far (60ish degrees and no rain [*fingers crossed*]).

Also, this will be a good opportunity to grab up some of Bauman's "world" famous apple cider and apple cider donuts, among other tasty treats in their shop. 

To get the discount we all (20+ people) have to go in at the same time so we will start getting tickets at about 11am, so arrive with a little time to spare. We will also be meeting at or inside the main store of the farm (attached is a little map showing the building and parking area).

Voted in tonight. Very excited to be a part of this group. Been loving all the times I helped them out every chance I could get for the past year. I hope to bring in fresh new ideas to move the group forward in the coming years. Big thanks to Kate Mann and the Gallagher's for helping and giving me the opportunity's to help out and get my foot in the door.

After a couple years of thinking I went for it and got my buddy Mario to do his magic in creating this amazing realistic marionette doll. I came to him with a basic wooded doll idea and days later he found me this amazingly creepy piece of art. Not affraid to say this was by far the most painful tattoo and life experience I have had to date. So many times I wanted to quit but I toughed it out the best I could for 6 hours.... If you are looking for an amazing artist I know the 3 best in salem!
